  "description": [
    "Letters from the counties on the Wabash toy that Edwards Lawrence J Crawford Clark and Edgar counties will on an average give two thirds of their votes against the con vention Payette and Mongomerv it is said will give email majorities against the convention bond about threefourths against it In Gallatin county the head quarters of slave principles it is said there will be from 150 to 200 votes against the convention In Pope and Franklin counties the oppo nents of the convention appear to be more nu merous than the most sanguine have ever anti cipated Union county it is confidently asserted will give a majority of about 50 against the conven tion A gentleman from Jackson county gives it as his opinion that the convention will have a majority of only 20 in that county In Randolph it is generally beieved that there will be a small majority in favor of the convention though the election of a part of the anticonvention tickets is considered cer tain In Monroe it is said the majority against the convention will be from 30 to 50 In St Clair some accounts say threefifths and other twothirds ot the votes will be"
